Slovak Advertisement Spending Rose 3 Percent in January-June

-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 
2011-07-27T15:21:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/slovak-advertisement-spending-rose-3-percent-in-january-june.html
Spending on advertisement in
Slovakia rose 3 percent in the first six months, compared with
the same period last year, according to TNS Slovakia, a market-
research company.  Companies led by the telecommunications industry bought
advertisement worth 403.5 million euros ($579.9 million) by
June, TNT Slovakia, a unit of Dublin-based  WPP Plc (WPP) , said today,
citing its own calculations using gross prices.  Television spending posted the biggest annual gain of 15
percent, Bratislava, Slovakia-based TNS Slovakia said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava News at 
